00:02:25.106 --> 00:02:26.730
I was part of the
first risk management

00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:31.864
group at Bankers Trust in 1986.

00:02:31.864 --> 00:02:33.780
No one else had a risk
management group as far

00:02:33.780 --> 00:02:34.330
as I know.

00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:40.590
Market risk management really
came to be in the late '80s.

00:02:40.590 --> 00:02:42.090
Credit risk management
had obviously

00:02:42.090 --> 00:02:45.700
been around in large financial
institutions the whole time.

00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:50.180
So our job is to make
sure that management

00:02:50.180 --> 00:02:51.660
knows what's on the books.

00:02:51.660 --> 00:02:54.910
So step one is, what is the
risk profile of the firm?

00:02:54.910 --> 00:02:57.582
How do I make sure
that management

00:02:57.582 --> 00:02:58.540
is informed about this?

00:02:58.540 --> 00:03:00.160
So it requires two things.

00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:02.520
One, I have to know
what the risk profile is

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:04.000
because I have to
know it in order

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:05.460
to be able to communicate it.

00:03:05.460 --> 00:03:08.210
But the second thing, equally
important, particularly

00:03:08.210 --> 00:03:11.880
important for you
guys and girls,

00:03:11.880 --> 00:03:16.310
is that you need to
be able to express

00:03:16.310 --> 00:03:19.860
relatively complex
concepts in simple words

00:03:19.860 --> 00:03:21.190
and pretty pictures.

00:03:21.190 --> 00:03:22.290
All right?

00:03:22.290 --> 00:03:25.900
