00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:36.360
So step one, make
sure management

00:04:36.360 --> 00:04:38.130
knows what the risk profile is.

00:04:38.130 --> 00:04:41.450
Step two, protect the firm
against unacceptably large

00:04:41.450 --> 00:04:42.290
concentrations.

00:04:42.290 --> 00:04:44.090
This is the subjective part.

00:04:44.090 --> 00:04:46.690
I can know the risk,
but how big is big?

00:04:46.690 --> 00:04:48.045
How much is too much?

00:04:48.045 --> 00:04:50.430
How much is too concentrated?

00:04:50.430 --> 00:04:53.550
If I have $1 million of
sensitivity per basis point,

00:04:53.550 --> 00:04:56.405
that's a 1/100th of
1% move in a rate.

00:04:56.405 --> 00:04:57.350
Is that big?

00:04:57.350 --> 00:04:58.920
Is that small?

00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:00.197
How do I know how much?

00:05:00.197 --> 00:05:02.280
How much of a particular
stock issue should I own?

00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:05.100
How much of a bond issue?

00:05:05.100 --> 00:05:06.610
How much futures open interest?

00:05:06.610 --> 00:05:08.800
How big a limit should I
have on this type of risk?

00:05:08.800 --> 00:05:12.121
That's where intuition and
experience come into play.

00:05:12.121 --> 00:05:13.620
So that's the second
part of our job

00:05:13.620 --> 00:05:17.040
is to protect against
unacceptably large losses.

00:05:17.040 --> 00:05:22.150
So the third, no
surprises, you can

00:05:22.150 --> 00:05:27.980
