And let's say I've
got a position vector,

00:47:17.140 --> 00:47:22.560
x_1, x_2, x_3, x_n.

00:47:28.730 --> 00:47:31.580
If I have all my
positions recorded

00:47:31.580 --> 00:47:34.450
as a vector-- this is asset
one, asset two, and this

00:47:34.450 --> 00:47:41.000
is in dollars-- and I have
the covariance structure,

00:47:41.000 --> 00:47:44.490
the variance of
this portfolio that

00:47:44.490 --> 00:47:47.460
has these assets and this
covariance structure-- this

00:47:47.460 --> 00:48:01.780
is where the magic happens--
is x transpose sigma x equals

00:48:01.780 --> 00:48:04.260
sigma squared hat portfolio.

00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:10.900
Now you really could
go work for a bank.

00:48:10.900 --> 00:48:14.580
This is how portfolio
variance, using

00:48:14.580 --> 00:48:17.640
the variance/covariance
method, is done.

