eigenvalue, you've got

01:10:16.300 --> 01:10:17.810
to fill in those observations.

01:10:17.810 --> 01:10:20.510
Which is why missing data
is a whole other thing

01:10:20.510 --> 01:10:22.999
we talk about.

01:10:22.999 --> 01:10:24.790
Again, I could spend
a lot of time on that.

01:10:24.790 --> 01:10:26.123
And I learned that the hard way.

01:10:28.690 --> 01:10:32.640
But anyway, so I take
this square root matrix,

01:10:32.640 --> 01:10:40.240
if I pre-multiply that square
root matrix by row after row

01:10:40.240 --> 01:10:46.700
of normals, I will
get out an array

01:10:46.700 --> 01:10:49.580
that has the same
covariance structure as that

01:10:49.580 --> 01:10:50.606
with which I started.

